President Obama has declared an emergency in the Commonwealth of Virginia and authorized federal aid to assist with the response efforts to Hurricane Sandy. The Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), will coordinate disaster relief efforts to help alleviate the hardships and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide necessary equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at a rate of 75 percent. Donald L. Keldsen has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.